\begin_layout Subsubsection*
6.5 Level 4 — Restricted
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Restricted information is highly sensitive data protected by strict federal or state requirements.
 Unauthorized disclosure or modification could result in severe legal penalties,
 loss of program access,
 loss of funding,
 or public safety impacts.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Examples
\series default
:
 Criminal Justice Information (CJI) as governed by CJIS Security Policy v6.0 Section 4,
 Protected Health Information (PHI) where applicable,
 active investigative data,
 administrative credentials,
 cryptographic keys.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Minimum Safeguards
\series default
:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Encryption
\series default
:
 All Information Operations Personnel shall protect Restricted data using cryptographic modules validated under the NIST Cryptographic Module Validation Program (CMVP) for data at rest and in transit,
 consistent with CJIS requirements.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Access
\series default
:
 All Information Operations Personnel shall enforce multi-factor authentication (MFA) for access to Restricted data systems,
 Restricted data repositories,
 and administrative functions,
 in accordance with 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:2.05"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Identification and Authentication Policy).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Exposure Controls
\series default
:
 The IT Director shall ensure Restricted data systems are not directly exposed to the public Internet without County-approved boundary protection and network segmentation consistent with CJIS requirements.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Auditing
\series default
:
 All Information Operations Personnel shall capture and retain audit records for access,
 modification,
 and deletion events in accordance with 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:2.11"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
,
 CJIS requirements for CJI,
 and the retention requirements defined in Section 6.9.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Subsubsection*
6.6 Data Handling and Stewardship
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Classification Assignment and Security Attributes
\series default
:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Department Heads shall assign the appropriate classification at creation or intake.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The IT Director shall ensure classification is associated as a security attribute on systems that support attribute-based access enforcement to support handling rules and auditability.
\end_layout

\end_deeper

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Labeling and Marking
\series default
:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The IT Director shall ensure that systems storing Confidential or Restricted data support classification labeling.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
All Information Operations Personnel shall apply classification labels to digital documents and physical media containing Confidential or Restricted information (e.g.,
 headers/footers,
 watermarking,
 media labels) to ensure personnel are aware of required handling and disclosure constraints.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Exception
\series default
:
 Systems or media formats that do not support labeling shall be documented by the IT Director,
 and the IT Director shall apply compensating controls.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Access Control and Need-to-Know
\series default
:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Department Heads shall ensure Confidential and Restricted data is accessible only to authorized users with a validated business need-to-know.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
All Information Operations Personnel shall enforce access through approved identity and access management controls consistent with 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:2.04"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 and 
\series bold
Policy 
