LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:2.05"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The IT Director shall ensure access is reviewed and adjusted when personnel roles change or upon termination of employment or contract.
\end_layout

\end_deeper

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Transmission Security
\series default
:
 All County Personnel shall not transmit Confidential or Restricted data over unprotected channels.
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Restricted Data
\series default
:
 All County Personnel shall transmit Restricted data only using County-approved secure methods that enforce strong encryption in transit (e.g.,
 approved VPN,
 TLS 1.2 or higher,
 or other approved secure protocols consistent with CJIS requirements).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Email Restrictions
\series default
:
 All County Personnel shall not use standard unencrypted email to transmit Restricted data.
 If transmission is explicitly authorized by the IT Director for business necessity,
 the IT Director shall designate an approved encryption method or secure delivery mechanism.
 Restricted CJI shall only be transmitted in accordance with the CJIS Security Policy.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Authorized Storage Locations and Cloud Security Assurance
\series default
:
 The IT Director shall approve all repositories and systems authorized for County data storage.
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Cloud Security Assurance
\series default
:
 The IT Director shall ensure vendors or cloud service providers hosting Confidential or Restricted County data are evaluated and governed through the vendor governance process defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.13"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Supply Chain Risk Management (SCRM) and Vendor Governance).
 Third-party authorizations (e.g.,
 FedRAMP,
 StateRAMP,
 SOC 2) may support due diligence but shall not be represented as automatically meeting CJIS Security Policy requirements or substituting for required CJIS agreements and addenda.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
CJI Cloud Requirements
\series default
:
 The IT Director shall ensure systems storing or processing CJI in cloud environments meet all CJIS Security Policy requirements for encryption,
 access control,
 auditing,
 personnel security,
 and agreement and oversight obligations applicable to the service model.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
CJI Data Sovereignty
\series default
:
 As an Elko County standard for CJIS risk control and audit defensibility,
 the IT Director shall ensure CJI is stored and processed only within the physical boundaries of an APB-member country and under the legal authority of an APB-member agency,
 unless permitted by the CSA/CSO and approved in writing by the LASO,
 with all required CJIS governing approvals documented.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
