\begin_layout Subsubsection*
6.9 Records Retention and Disposition
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The IT Director shall ensure retention periods are applied in accordance with NRS 239.125 and the Nevada Local Government Records Retention Schedule.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
IT Security Audit Records
\series default
:
 The IT Director shall retain IT security logs,
 including access control and audit logs,
 for a minimum of three (3) calendar years from the end of the calendar year in which the review or audit was concluded,
 per the applicable Nevada Local Government Records Retention Schedule for IT Security Audit Records (currently LRDA 20071728).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
CJIS Audit Records
\series default
:
 For CJIS audit records,
 the IT Director shall apply the greater of the CJIS minimum retention period or the applicable Nevada retention requirement.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Destruction Standards
\series default
:
 The IT Director shall ensure destruction of confidential records complies with NAC 239.165.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Legal Holds
\series default
:
 The IT Director shall suspend retention and disposition actions for Information Operations records during litigation holds,
 public records preservation requirements,
 audits,
 or other legal hold events.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*
6.10 Public Records and Disclosure Obligations
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The IT Director shall ensure security classification is not treated as an automatic exemption from disclosure.
 The IT Director shall ensure public records requests under NRS 239 are handled through the County's established legal review process.
 When classification controls appear to conflict with a public records obligation,
 the District Attorney's Office shall provide binding guidance.
\end_layout

